div.div:
Each module has the ability to put the pod into a braking or emergency braking state by asserting BEGIN_BRAKE or BEGIN_E_BRAKE, including the WCM via remote dashboard messages.
MCM:
Controls halbach wheels using the control algorithm that uses wheel RPM, pod forward velocity, current distance down the tube and the proximity sensor position values as inputs
VSM:
Keeps track of ambient pressure and temperature points, can disconnect battery pack?
VNM:
Keeps track of distance down the tube, velocity, and acceleration. Will signal system to enter BRAKE when it reaches a certain distance down the tube
BCM:

div.font: When not executing "Max Braking Protocol", velocity obtained via reflective strips is compared to the values in array TRAJECTORY_BRAKING_SPEEDS and the braking intensity is adjusted automatically (difference multiplied by TRAJECTORY_BRAKING_SPEEDS_P_GAIN).

Max Braking Protocol is entered when braking intensity reaches 99%, automatically if the system invoked BEGIN_E_BRAKE, or other faults are detected such as losing track of the reflective strips (BRAKING_ERROR enum).

div.span: Anti-Lock braking will automatically reduce braking intensity temporarily to avoid wheel lockup, it can be disabled on the dashboard.
